(A and B) Example traces showing effects of 100 mM CBDV on epileptiform LFPs induced by Mg 2+ -free conditions (A) or 100 mM 4-AP (B) in the CA1 region. 
The black bar represents amplitude as corrected for inherent rundown (see Methods); the dotted line below represents control burst duration. 
Scale in (A): 100 mV/200 ms; (B): 150 mV/200 ms. (C–H) Effects of CBDV on amplitude (C and F), duration (D and G) and frequency (E and H) of epileptiform LFPs induced by Mg 2+ -free conditions (C–E) or 100 mM 4-AP (F–H). 
Data are presented as mean Ϯ SEM normalized to control (pre-drug) conditions and corrected for background changes where appropriate (see Methods). 
